---
import TopNav from "../../components/TopNav.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta name="robots" content="noindex, nofollow" />
    <title>Momentum - Billy Carlson</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles/case-study.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <TopNav />
    
    <main class="case-study-page">
      <!-- Hero Section -->
      <section class="case-hero">
        <h1 class="case-title">Momentum</h1>
        <p class="case-lede">
          Transforming KPMG's legacy reporting workflow into a governed, collaborative product inside One Port.
        </p>
        <div class="case-meta-grid">
          <div class="meta-item">
            <div class="meta-label">Client</div>
            <div class="meta-value">KPMG Canada · Ignition</div>
          </div>
          <div class="meta-item">
            <div class="meta-label">Scope</div>
            <div class="meta-value">Product strategy, workflow architecture, UX leadership, cross-practice alignment, MVP definition for integration within One Port</div>
          </div>
          <div class="meta-item">
            <div class="meta-label">Role & Contributions</div>
            <div class="meta-value role-multiline">Design Lead & Player/Coach
Experience strategy, fidelity progression, collaboration model, UX patterns, Builder Mode workflows, prototype → MVP partnership with engineering</div>
          </div>
          <div class="meta-item">
            <div class="meta-label">Timeline</div>
            <div class="meta-value">2024 – 2025 (in progress)</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Overview Section -->
      <section class="case-section">
        <div class="section-text">
          <p>
            Momentum reimagines KPMG's manual 360 Review process as a living product experience, shifting value creation from a single, end-of-engagement deliverable to ongoing strategic insight across the entire lifecycle of client work.
          </p>
          <p>
            Instead of PDF reports assembled at the finish line, Momentum drives forward progress throughout the engagement — with structure, governance, and collaboration built directly into One Port.
          </p>
          <p>
            The result is an MVP that internal teams can use, test, and scale — replacing fragmented tooling with a shared definition of both the workflow and the value.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="placeholder-image geometric-pattern" style="width: 100%; aspect-ratio: 16/9; margin-top: 32px;" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      </section>

      <!-- tl;dr Section -->
      <section class="case-section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <span class="section-label">TL;DR</span>
          <h2 class="section-title">tl;dr</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="tldr-layout">
          <div class="tldr-content">
            <div class="section-text">
              <p>
                KPMG's legacy reporting process was functional but unsustainable: manual, siloed, over-dependent on expert intervention, and too often delivered after strategic opportunities had passed.
              </p>
              <p>
                Momentum changes the timeline:
              </p>
              <ul>
                <li>Insight starts earlier</li>
                <li>Collaboration happens in-platform</li>
                <li>Work becomes reusable</li>
                <li>Confidence can be operationalized</li>
              </ul>
              <p>
                The MVP introduces:
              </p>
              <ul>
                <li>Builder Mode</li>
                <li>Structured screener workflows</li>
                <li>Data ingestion paths (API → Excel → OCR)</li>
                <li>Publishing governance</li>
                <li>Entity-level ownership inside One Port</li>
              </ul>
              <p>
                Momentum replaces "deliverable-first" with "progress-first."
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="tldr-metrics">
            <div class="tldr-metric">
              <div class="tldr-metric-value">548+</div>
              <div class="tldr-metric-label">screens designed</div>
            </div>
            <div class="tldr-metric">
              <div class="tldr-metric-value">665</div>
              <div class="tldr-metric-label">unique components</div>
            </div>
            <div class="tldr-metric">
              <div class="tldr-metric-value">66</div>
              <div class="tldr-metric-label">pages of product and brand guidelines</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- The Problem Section -->
      <section class="case-section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <span class="section-label">THE PROBLEM</span>
          <h2 class="section-title">The structural challenge of manual reporting</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="section-text">
          <p>
            The 360 Review is a proven consulting asset — but the delivery model hadn't kept pace with modern expectations:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Reports built manually in Microsoft Word</li>
            <li>Scattered spreadsheets and SMEs as single points of failure</li>
            <li>Context lost between service lines</li>
            <li>Late delivery minimizing strategic impact</li>
            <li>No ownership model for collaboration</li>
            <li>Repeating the same effort annually</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            This wasn't a UX problem.<br />
            It was a structural one.
          </p>
          <p>
            The product had to absorb the complexity — not the user.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="placeholder-image product-mockup" style="width: 100%; aspect-ratio: 16/9; margin-top: 32px;" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      </section>

      <!-- Outcome Section -->
      <section class="case-section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <span class="section-label">OUTCOME</span>
          <h2 class="section-title">Momentum reframes reporting as a platform capability</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="section-text">
          <p>
            Momentum reframes reporting as a platform capability, not an artifact.
          </p>
          <p>
            Momentum gives teams a shared toolset, a shared model of progress, and a shared language for how insight becomes value.
          </p>
        </div>

        <table class="comparison-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Before</th>
              <th>After</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>One person assembles a report at the end</td>
              <td>Teams build insight in stages throughout</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Files live in email / desktop</td>
              <td>Work lives inside One Port</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>No reusability across years</td>
              <td>Annual carry-over context</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Emergent strategy</td>
              <td>Structured collaboration</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Static PDF</td>
              <td>Governed publishing pipeline</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <div class="leadership-quote">
          <p>"Momentum finally feels like a product with direction — not just a process we inherit."</p>
          <cite>— Placeholder, KPMG Leadership</cite>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Strategy Section -->
      <section class="case-section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <span class="section-label">STRATEGY</span>
          <h2 class="section-title">Audience Ecosystem</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="section-text">
          <p>
            Momentum needed to support a multi-stakeholder environment without fragmenting the experience:
          </p>
        </div>

        <table class="comparison-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Audience</th>
              <th>Challenge</th>
              <th>Need</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>Engagement Partners</td>
              <td>Insight comes too late</td>
              <td>Lead earlier with confidence</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>SMEs & Service Practitioners</td>
              <td>Work becomes invisible</td>
              <td>Structured collaboration</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Analysts / Juniors</td>
              <td>High barrier to entry</td>
              <td>Scaffolding + clarity</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Clients</td>
              <td>Overwhelming outputs</td>
              <td>Context, narrative, and timing</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <div class="section-text">
          <p>
            We balanced these needs across the engagement timeline instead of treating them sequentially.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="section-title" style="margin: 64px 0 24px;">Design Pillars</h2>
        <div class="section-text">
          <p>
            Our strategic pillars anchored every decision:
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="margin: 48px 0;">
          <div style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
            <h3 style="font-size: var(--step-1); font-weight: 600; margin: 0 0 16px; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--text); line-height: 1.3;">1. Clarity Over Control</h3>
            <div class="section-text">
              <p>
                Tools that guide without forcing, ensuring the product supports judgment rather than replaces it.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
            <h3 style="font-size: var(--step-1); font-weight: 600; margin: 0 0 16px; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--text); line-height: 1.3;">2. Momentum Over Completion</h3>
            <div class="section-text">
              <p>
                Progress is a product outcome. Completion is a milestone, not the value.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 style="font-size: var(--step-1); font-weight: 600; margin: 0 0 16px; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--text); line-height: 1.3;">3. Structure Without Script</h3>
            <div class="section-text">
              <p>
                Prompts, defaults, and guided paths — without reducing expertise to templates.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Process Section -->
      <section class="case-section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <span class="section-label">PROCESS</span>
          <h2 class="section-title">Multi-stage progression from process to product</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="section-text">
          <div style="margin-bottom: 32px;">
            <h4 style="font-size: var(--step-1); font-weight: 500; margin: 0 0 12px; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--text);">1. Prototype for Alignment</h4>
            <p>
              We started low-fidelity to define what Momentum is, what it isn't, and where it fits in One Port.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div style="margin-bottom: 32px;">
            <h4 style="font-size: var(--step-1); font-weight: 500; margin: 0 0 12px; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--text);">2. Workshops Across Practices</h4>
            <p>
              Tax, Assurance, Audit, and platform engineering established shared definitions of ownership and entry points.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div style="margin-bottom: 32px;">
            <h4 style="font-size: var(--step-1); font-weight: 500; margin: 0 0 12px; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--text);">3. UX + Architecture Iteration</h4>
            <p>
              We surfaced friction patterns and learned where practitioners needed support vs autonomy.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div style="margin-bottom: 32px;">
            <h4 style="font-size: var(--step-1); font-weight: 500; margin: 0 0 12px; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--text);">4. MVP Scope & Engineering Partnership</h4>
            <p>
              Feature cuts and sequencing preserved strategic intent without over-building.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h4 style="font-size: var(--step-1); font-weight: 500; margin: 0 0 12px; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--text);">5. Build Integration</h4>
            <p>
              Worked alongside engineering to translate experience concepts into buildable pathways tied to platform constraints.
            </p>
          </div>

          <p style="margin-top: 32px;">
            This was executed as a player/coach contribution — designing while raising the team's ability to move from ambiguity to alignment.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="placeholder-image product-mockup" style="width: 100%; aspect-ratio: 16/9; margin-top: 32px;" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      </section>

      <!-- Solutions Section -->
      <section class="case-section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <span class="section-label">SOLUTIONS</span>
          <h2 class="section-title">Report Creation Model</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="section-text">
          <p>
            A report is created at the Entity or Engagement level inside One Port, enforcing:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Ownership</li>
            <li>Eligibility</li>
            <li>Governance</li>
            <li>Visibility</li>
            <li>Reusability</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Creation is no longer an isolated act — it's foundational to structure and scale.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="placeholder-image geometric-pattern" style="width: 100%; aspect-ratio: 16/9; margin-top: 32px;" aria-hidden="true"></div>

        <h2 class="section-title" style="margin: 64px 0 24px;">Builder Mode</h2>
        <div class="section-text">
          <p>
            The core of the experience.
          </p>
          <p>
            Builder Mode allows practitioners to build insight progressively, collaboratively, and transparently — before, during, and after client conversations.
          </p>
          <p>
            Builder Mode introduces:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Screener workflows (context before content)</li>
            <li>Section-by-section drafting</li>
            <li>Collaboration + role visibility</li>
            <li>Inline guidance and scaffolding</li>
            <li>Right-rail knowledge capture</li>
            <li>In-product narrative development</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            This is the cultural transformation: the report becomes a workspace, not a document.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="placeholder-image geometric-pattern" style="width: 100%; aspect-ratio: 16/9; margin-top: 32px;" aria-hidden="true"></div>

        <h2 class="section-title" style="margin: 64px 0 24px;">Data Ingestion Architecture</h2>
        <div class="section-text">
          <p>
            We architected three ingestion paths to prevent client maturity from breaking the product:
          </p>
          <ol style="margin: 24px 0; padding-left: 24px; line-height: 1.8;">
            <li>CaseWare API (ideal state; structured)</li>
            <li>Excel Templates (standard operating reality)</li>
            <li>OCR PDF (fallback so no client is blocked)</li>
          </ol>
          <p>
            This approach allows Momentum to scale immediately — without requiring clients to.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="placeholder-image product-mockup" style="width: 100%; aspect-ratio: 16/9; margin-top: 32px;" aria-hidden="true"></div>

        <h2 class="section-title" style="margin: 64px 0 24px;">Publishing Governance</h2>
        <div class="section-text">
          <p>
            Publication is a guided step with:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Permissioning & ownership</li>
            <li>Readiness checks</li>
            <li>Governance standards</li>
            <li>Traceability</li>
            <li>Client Portal integration</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            "Publish" becomes a decision — not a file save.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="placeholder-image product-mockup" style="width: 100%; aspect-ratio: 16/9; margin-top: 32px;" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      </section>

      <!-- Insights Section -->
      <section class="case-section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <span class="section-label">INSIGHTS</span>
          <h2 class="section-title">Building clarity through structured collaboration</h2>
        </div>
        
        <div style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
          <h3 style="font-size: var(--step-1); font-weight: 600; margin: 0 0 16px; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--text); line-height: 1.3;">
            When maturity varies, UX must absorb complexity.
          </h3>
          <div class="section-text">
            <p>
              We focused on pathways instead of ideal states.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
          <h3 style="font-size: var(--step-1); font-weight: 600; margin: 0 0 16px; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--text); line-height: 1.3;">
            Value comes from timing, not volume.
          </h3>
          <div class="section-text">
            <p>
              Arriving earlier mattered more than adding more content.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 style="font-size: var(--step-1); font-weight: 600; margin: 0 0 16px; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--text); line-height: 1.3;">
            Clarity is an accelerant.
          </h3>
          <div class="section-text">
            <p>
              Well-designed scaffolding triggered cross-practice collaboration faster than new features did.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Next Steps Section -->
      <section class="case-section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <span class="section-label">FUTURE OPPORTUNITIES</span>
          <h2 class="section-title">Future Opportunities</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="section-text">
          <ul>
            <li>AI summarization of Builder Mode progress</li>
            <li>Annual carry-forward engagement memory</li>
            <li>Patterns library for domain-specific insight surfacing</li>
            <li>Integration with Interval data visualization</li>
            <li>Structured narrative generation for clients</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Momentum is positioned not as a delivery mechanism — but as a capability surface within One Port.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Positioning Section -->
      <section class="case-section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <span class="section-label">POSITIONING</span>
          <h2 class="section-title">Positioning</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="section-text">
          <p>
            This case study represents how I lead:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>I enter ambiguity and establish direction.</li>
            <li>I build clarity before fidelity.</li>
            <li>I design for behavior change, not just interface change.</li>
            <li>I work as a player/coach: strategic where needed, hands-on where necessary.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Momentum reflects the work I want to do more of: transform legacy processes into products that scale value.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  .case-study-page {
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 60px 80px 80px;
    width: 100%;
  }

  /* Hero Section */
  .case-hero {
    margin-bottom: 80px;
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  .case-title {
    font-size: 48px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text);
    margin: 0 0 30px;
    font-family: 'Instrument Serif', serif;
  }

  .case-lede {
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2rem);
    line-height: 1.3;
    color: var(--text);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-family: 'Instrument Serif', serif;
    margin: 0 0 48px;
  }

  .case-meta-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: 48px;
    padding-top: 48px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline);
  }

  .meta-item {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 8px;
  }

  .meta-label {
    font-size: var(--step--1);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .meta-value {
    font-size: var(--step-0);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--text);
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
  }

  .meta-value.role-multiline {
    white-space: pre-line;
  }

  /* Sections */
  .case-section {
    margin-bottom: 80px;
    padding-top: 40px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline);
  }

  .section-header {
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }

  .section-label {
    display: block;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--red);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
  }

  .section-title {
    font-size: 32px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text);
    margin: 0;
    font-family: 'Instrument Serif', serif;
  }

  .section-text {
    font-size: var(--step-0);
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--text);
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    margin-bottom: 48px;
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .section-text p {
    margin: 0 0 28px;
  }

  .section-text p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .section-text ul,
  .section-text ol {
    margin: 24px 0;
    padding-left: 24px;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .section-text li {
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  /* Two-column tl;dr layout */
  .tldr-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 280px;
    gap: 0;
    margin: 48px 0;
    position: relative;
  }

  .tldr-content {
    min-width: 0;
    padding-right: 48px;
  }

  .tldr-metrics {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 32px;
    padding-left: 48px;
    border-left: 1px dashed #bdbdbd;
  }

  .tldr-metric {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 4px;
  }

  .tldr-metric-value {
    font-size: var(--step-3);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-family: 'Instrument Serif', serif;
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .tldr-metric-label {
    font-size: var(--step--1);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
  }

  /* Tables */
  .comparison-table {
    width: 100%;
    margin: 64px 0;
    border-collapse: separate;
    border-spacing: 0;
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    background: var(--bg);
    border-radius: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
  }

  .comparison-table th {
    font-size: var(--step--1);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--white);
    background: var(--red);
    padding: 24px 32px;
    text-align: left;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--hairline);
    position: relative;
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
  }

  .comparison-table th:not(:last-child)::after {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    right: 0;
    top: 25%;
    bottom: 25%;
    width: 1px;
    background: var(--hairline);
  }

  .comparison-table td {
    font-size: var(--step-0);
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--text);
    padding: 24px 32px;
    text-align: left;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
    transition: background-color 0.15s ease;
    vertical-align: top;
  }

  .comparison-table tbody tr:last-child td {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  /* Quote/Testimonial */
  .leadership-quote {
    margin: 64px 0;
    padding: 32px;
    background: var(--red);
    border: none;
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
  }

  .leadership-quote p {
    font-size: var(--step-1);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--white);
    font-style: normal;
    margin: 0 0 20px;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .leadership-quote cite {
    font-size: var(--step--1);
    color: var(--white);
    font-style: normal;
    display: block;
    font-weight: 400;
    opacity: 0.9;
  }

  /* Placeholder images */
  .placeholder-image {
    width: 100%;
    height: 400px;
    background: var(--grey-dark);
    display: block;
    position: relative;
  }

  .placeholder-image.geometric-pattern {
    background: 
      repeating-linear-gradient(
        0deg,
        transparent,
        transparent 24px,
        var(--grey-medium) 24px,
        var(--grey-medium) 25px
      ),
      repeating-linear-gradient(
        90deg,
        transparent,
